  "text": "In the Firefox repository (firefox--871325b8), the core Servo-based CSS style resolution pipeline is implemented under layout/style/ with the following key files:\n\n1. layout/style/ServoStyleSet.h and layout/style/ServoStyleSet.cpp — Define the `ServoStyleSet` class (declared at line 107 of the header), which is the main C++ entry point for style resolution. It coordinates style computation by calling into the Servo style engine.\n\n2. layout/style/ServoBindings.h — Declares the FFI boundary between Gecko (C++) and Servo (Rust). It exposes `Servo_*` and `Gecko_*` functions via cbindgen-generated bindings, with functions like `Servo_CounterStyleRule_GetDescriptorCssText` and macros expanding to `Servo_StyleSet_*RuleChanged`, etc.\n\n3. layout/style/RestyleManager.h — Declares the `RestyleManager` class (at line 202), which schedules and manages style recalculation in response to DOM mutations and other changes that require style to be recomputed.\n\n4. layout/style/ServoUtils.h — Provides utility functions for Servo traversal state, including `IsInServoTraversal()` (line 24), which checks whether a Servo parallel style traversal is currently active.\n\n5. layout/style/moz.build — The build system file listing all style system source files compiled into the layout/style/ module."
}

